    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written to the plan file:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 changes total — 4 new files, 1 small edit.**\n\n### Files to create\n\n1. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation (no external deps):\n   - `Geo` interface with 7 optional string fields\n   - `COUNTRY_NAMES` map for 10 ISO codes (AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US)\n   - `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel headers, falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for Cloudflare, derives `country` from the map\n   - `geo({ headers }): Geo` — convenience wrapper mirroring `userAgent`\n   - `isInRegion(geo, regions): boolean` — case-insensitive countryCode check\n   - `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2): number` — Haversine formula in km\n\n2. **`packages/next/geo.js`** — Thin CommonJS entry, exact same dual-export pattern as `server.js`\n\n3. **`packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — TypeScript re-exports from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`, same pattern as `server.d.ts`\n\n4. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Tests with `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` covering all functions, all 10 country codes, NY→London distance (±50 km), Cloudflare fallback, missing headers, and case-insensitive region matching\n\n### File to modify\n\n5. **`packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` into the `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical order: `g` between `f` and `h`)\n\n### Verification steps\n1. `pnpm --filter=next types` — type check\n2. `pnpm --filter=next build` — compile to `dist/`\n3. Run `geo.test.ts` via `node:test`\n4. Smoke: `node -e \"console.log(Object.keys(require('./packages/next/geo.js')))\"`",
